<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,1848,2017]" lastBlockId="7.[151,1436,151,573]" lastPageId="7" lastPageNumber="482" pageId="6" pageNumber="481">
This species has an elongated lorica with unevenly curved anterior aperture margins in lateral view, shows high similarity with the typical form of 
<taxonomicName authority="Segers &amp; Chittapun, 2001" authorityName="Segers &amp; Chittapun" authorityYear="2001" box="[540,1106,1884,1909]" class="Eurotatoria" family="Lepadellidae" genus="Colurella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ploima" pageId="6" pageNumber="481" phylum="Rotifera" rank="species" species="psammophila">
<emphasis box="[540,804,1885,1909]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="481">Colurella psammophila</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Segers, H. &amp; Chittapun, S." box="[811,1106,1884,1909]" pageId="6" pageNumber="481" pagination="65 - 71" refId="ref7913" refString="Segers, H. &amp; Chittapun, S. (2001) The interstitial Rotifera of a tropical freshwater peat swamp on Phuket Island, Thailand. Belgian Journal of Zoology, 131, 65 - 71." type="journal article" year="2001">Segers &amp; Chittapun, 2001</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, but differs from the latter by (1) greater lorica length: 
<quantity box="[428,521,1921,1945]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.18" pageId="6" pageNumber="481" unit="mm" value="91.8">91.8 µm</quantity>
<emphasis box="[527,550,1921,1944]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="481">vs</emphasis>
. 
<quantity box="[564,677,1920,1945]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.3" metricValueMax="8.1" metricValueMin="6.5" pageId="6" pageNumber="481" unit="mm" value="73.0" valueMax="81.0" valueMin="65.0">65–81 µm</quantity>
in Thai specimens (
<bibRefCitation author="Segers, H. &amp; Chittapun, S." box="[900,1191,1920,1945]" pageId="6" pageNumber="481" pagination="65 - 71" refId="ref7913" refString="Segers, H. &amp; Chittapun, S. (2001) The interstitial Rotifera of a tropical freshwater peat swamp on Phuket Island, Thailand. Belgian Journal of Zoology, 131, 65 - 71." type="journal article" year="2001">Segers &amp; Chittapun, 2001</bibRefCitation>
) and 70.0– 
<quantity box="[1317,1408,1920,1945]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.15" pageId="6" pageNumber="481" unit="mm" value="81.5">81.5 µm</quantity>
in Chinese specimens (this study); (2) distinctly higher ratio of lorica length/height: 1.87 
<emphasis box="[1153,1176,1958,1981]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="481">vs</emphasis>
. 
<quantity box="[1192,1336,1957,1982]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.0386" metricValueMax="4.2672" metricValueMin="3.81" pageId="6" pageNumber="481" unit="in" value="1.5899999999999999" valueMax="1.68" valueMin="1.5">1.50–1.68 in</quantity>
Chinese specimens of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Segers &amp; Chittapun" authorityYear="2001" box="[314,503,1993,2017]" class="Eurotatoria" family="Lepadellidae" genus="Colurella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ploima" pageId="6" pageNumber="481" phylum="Rotifera" rank="species" species="psammophila">
<emphasis box="[314,503,1993,2017]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="481">C. psammophila</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; (3) toes slightly longer: 
<quantity box="[811,909,1993,2017]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.22" pageId="6" pageNumber="481" unit="mm" value="42.2">42.2 µm</quantity>
<emphasis box="[920,943,1993,2016]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="481">vs</emphasis>
. 
<quantity box="[963,1081,1993,2017]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.4" metricValueMax="3.8" metricValueMin="3.0" pageId="6" pageNumber="481" unit="mm" value="34.0" valueMax="38.0" valueMin="30.0">30–38 µm</quantity>
in Thai specimens (
<bibRefCitation author="Segers, H. &amp; Chittapun, S." lastPageId="7" lastPageNumber="482" pageId="6" pageNumber="481" pagination="65 - 71" refId="ref7913" refString="Segers, H. &amp; Chittapun, S. (2001) The interstitial Rotifera of a tropical freshwater peat swamp on Phuket Island, Thailand. Belgian Journal of Zoology, 131, 65 - 71." type="journal article" year="2001">Segers &amp; Chittapun, 2001</bibRefCitation>
) and 33.0– 
<quantity box="[459,552,152,176]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.77" pageId="7" pageNumber="482" unit="mm" value="37.7">37.7 µm</quantity>
in Chinese specimens; (4) without median keel in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Segers &amp; Chittapun" authorityYear="2001" box="[1122,1341,151,176]" class="Eurotatoria" family="Lepadellidae" genus="Colurella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ploima" pageId="7" pageNumber="482" phylum="Rotifera" rank="species" species="psammophila">
<emphasis box="[1122,1148,152,175]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="482">C.</emphasis>
cf. 
<emphasis box="[1190,1341,152,176]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="482">psammophila</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis box="[1348,1371,153,176]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="482">vs</emphasis>
. with a conspicuous median keel in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Segers &amp; Chittapun" authorityYear="2001" box="[487,671,188,212]" class="Eurotatoria" family="Lepadellidae" genus="Colurella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ploima" pageId="7" pageNumber="482" phylum="Rotifera" rank="species" species="psammophila">
<emphasis box="[487,671,188,212]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="482">C. psammophila</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1436,151,573]" pageId="7" pageNumber="482">
Besides, the elongated lancet-shaped lorica also shows superficial similarity with 
<taxonomicName authority="(Lucks, 1912)" authorityName="Lucks" authorityYear="1912" baseAuthorityName="Lucks" baseAuthorityYear="1912" class="Eurotatoria" family="Lepadellidae" genus="Colurella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ploima" pageId="7" pageNumber="482" phylum="Rotifera" rank="subSpecies" species="colurus" subSpecies="compressa">
<emphasis box="[1113,1436,224,248]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="482">Colurella colurus compressa</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Lucks, R." box="[159,303,260,285]" pageId="7" pageNumber="482" refId="ref7749" refString="Lucks, R. (1912) Zur Rotatorienfauna Westpreussens. Westpreussisch Botanisch-Zoologischer Verein (ed.), A. W. Kafemann, Danzig, 207 pp." type="book" year="1912">Lucks, 1912</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. It differs from the latter mostly by (1) the outline of its anterior aperture margin being undulate, not evenly curved, with a shallow concavity in its lower ventral third, whereas, the head aperture margins are smoothly curved in 
<taxonomicName authority="(Lucks, 1912)" authorityName="Lucks" authorityYear="1912" baseAuthorityName="Lucks" baseAuthorityYear="1912" box="[263,673,332,357]" class="Eurotatoria" family="Lepadellidae" genus="Colurella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ploima" pageId="7" pageNumber="482" phylum="Rotifera" rank="subSpecies" species="colurus" subSpecies="compressa">
<emphasis box="[263,506,332,356]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="482">C. colurus compressa</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Lucks, R." box="[521,665,332,357]" pageId="7" pageNumber="482" refId="ref7749" refString="Lucks, R. (1912) Zur Rotatorienfauna Westpreussens. Westpreussisch Botanisch-Zoologischer Verein (ed.), A. W. Kafemann, Danzig, 207 pp." type="book" year="1912">Lucks, 1912</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
; (2) toes spread in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Segers &amp; Chittapun" authorityYear="2001" box="[886,1106,332,357]" class="Eurotatoria" family="Lepadellidae" genus="Colurella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ploima" pageId="7" pageNumber="482" phylum="Rotifera" rank="species" species="psammophila">
<emphasis box="[886,912,332,355]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="482">C.</emphasis>
cf. 
<emphasis box="[955,1106,332,356]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="482">psammophila</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, which are usually appressed in 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Lucks" baseAuthorityYear="1912" box="[180,421,368,392]" class="Eurotatoria" family="Lepadellidae" genus="Colurella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ploima" pageId="7" pageNumber="482" phylum="Rotifera" rank="subSpecies" species="colurus" subSpecies="compressa">
<emphasis box="[180,421,368,392]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="482">C. colurus compressa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1436,151,573]" pageId="7" pageNumber="482">
This 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bory De St. Vincent" authorityYear="1823" box="[258,364,404,428]" class="Eurotatoria" family="Lepadellidae" genus="Colurella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ploima" pageId="7" pageNumber="482" phylum="Rotifera" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[258,364,404,428]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="482">Colurella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
only occurred in the mangrove swamp in 
<date box="[855,1036,404,429]" pageId="7" pageNumber="482" value="2007-12">December 2007</date>
(
<tableCitation box="[1053,1124,404,429]" captionStart="TABLE 1" captionStartId="12.[147,233,571,594]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="TABLE 1. The distribution and ecological characteristic of studied Colurella species in China Sa: salinity; WT: water temperature; WD: water depth; DS: distance from shore" httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/F2C05A93FF91FFFFFF09FDEB72FCE450" pageId="7" pageNumber="482" tableUuid="F2C05A93FF91FFFFFF09FDEB72FCE450">Tab. 1</tableCitation>
) with one specimen. More specimens are needed to settle its taxonomic status.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1436,151,573]" pageId="7" pageNumber="482">
Measurements. Body (N = 
<specimenCount box="[515,621,476,501]" pageId="7" pageNumber="482" type="female">1 female</specimenCount>
): Lorica length 
<quantity box="[806,904,476,501]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.18" pageId="7" pageNumber="482" unit="mm" value="91.8">91.8 µm</quantity>
, lorica height 49.0 µm, lorica width 
<quantity box="[1333,1431,476,501]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.27" pageId="7" pageNumber="482" unit="mm" value="42.7">42.7 µm</quantity>
, anterior aperture width 
<quantity box="[416,512,512,536]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.91" pageId="7" pageNumber="482" unit="mm" value="39.1">39.1 µm</quantity>
, second foot pseudosegment 
<quantity box="[843,924,511,536]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.7" pageId="7" pageNumber="482" unit="mm" value="6.7">6.7 µm</quantity>
, third foot pseudosegment 
<quantity box="[1230,1312,512,536]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.2" pageId="7" pageNumber="482" unit="mm" value="8.2">8.2 µm</quantity>
, toe length 
<quantity box="[151,247,548,573]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.22" pageId="7" pageNumber="482" unit="mm" value="42.2">42.2 µm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
